videoSnippet.title: Alekhine Would be Proud || Caruana vs Carlsen || MC Invitational (2020)
videoSnippet.description:

Fabiano Caruana vs Magnus Carlsen
Magnus Carlsen Invitational GAME 1, 22.4.2020
Alekhine's defence, four pawns attack, fianchetto variation (B03)

1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. c4 Nb6 5. f4 g6 6. Nc3 Bg7 7. Be3 Be6 8. Nf3 O-O 9. b3 dxe5 10. dxe5 Nc6 11. Ne4 f6 12. Nc5 Qc8 13. exf6 Bxf6 14. Be2 Rd8 15. Qc1 Bf5 16. O-O Nd7 17. Nd3 Bxa1 18. Qxa1 Nf6 19. Nde5 Nxe5 20. Nxe5 Qe6 21. Bd4 Nd7 22. h3 Nxe5 23. Bxe5 c6 24. Qc3 h5 25. Re1 Kf7 26. Qg3 Rd2 27. Bf3 Rd3 28. Qg5 Rad8 29. Kf2 Rd2+ 30. Kg3 R8d3 31. Qh6 Bxh3 32. Kh4 Rxg2

World Champion Magnus Carlsen takes on world blitz no. 1 Hikaru Nakamura today in a 4-game rapid match as the $250,000 Magnus Carlsen Invitational begins. Usually that pairing would eclipse any other match, but 16-year-old Alireza Firouzja taking on world no. 3 Ding Liren is almost as mouth-watering. Can Alireza continue in the form that saw him beat Magnus in the Banter Blitz Cup final? All the games will be streamed live on chess24 with commentary in 9 languages as a new age of online chess begins.
